<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-92-0476 </DOCNO><TEXT>With the discovery of gas reserves estimated at around 100 billion cum in the upper Amazon, the Brazilian Government has unveiled a nationalplan for gas production reaching 24 million cu.m/day by 1991. Plans bythe state oil company Petrobras to transport gas by pipeline to a giantmining complex and to cities for electricity generation are discussed,and the priorities for using the gas for injecting into oil wells toincrease flow, as a substitute for LPG, as raw material for petrochemicalsand finally as substitute for oil derivatives are outlined.</TEXT></DOC>